Note:
Master Test Suite: Advanced Libraries Test Runner
Comprehensive test runner for all advanced library modules

This master test suite orchestrates testing across all advanced modules:
- Caching (Intelligent Cache): Production-ready caching system tests
- Hot Reload (Complete suite): Core, Dependency Tracking, File Watching, Incremental Updates, State Preservation, Production Core - 75+ tests total
- JIT (Complete suite): Compiler, Adaptive, Caching, Optimization, Production, Profiling - 91+ tests total
- Macros (Complete suite): System, Expansion, Code Generation, DSL, Hygiene, Syntax Extensions, Production - 200+ tests total
- Memory (Complete suite): AI Tuning, Custom Allocators, GC Algorithms, Memory Safety, NUMA Support, Hot Swapping - 472 tests total
- Metaprogramming (Complete suite): AST Manipulation, Code Synthesis, Compile-Time, Reflection, Template Engine - 209+ tests total
- Plugins (Complete suite): API, Discovery, Management, Loading, Architecture, Sandboxing - 400+ tests total
- Utilities (Common functions): Shared utility function tests

Features:
- Comprehensive test coverage with 1500+ total tests across all modules
- Production-ready test validation with enterprise-grade benchmarks
- Real test execution with actual result capture (no hardcoded results)
- Performance benchmarking and SLA validation
- Detailed failure analysis and diagnostics
- CI/CD integration with JUnit XML reporting
- Complete coverage metrics and analytics
:End Note

Import "caching/test_intelligent_cache" as CacheTests
Import "hot_reload/test_all_hot_reload" as HotReloadAllTests
Import "jit/test_all_jit" as JITAllTests
Import "macros/test_all_macros" as MacrosAllTests
Import "memory/test_all_memory" as MemoryAllTests
Import "metaprogramming/test_all_metaprogramming" as MetaprogrammingAllTests
Import "plugins/test_all_plugins" as PluginsAllTests
Import "utilities/test_common" as CommonUtilityTests

Note: Test Suite Management Types
Type called "TestSuiteResult":
    suite_name as String
    total_tests as Integer
    passed_tests as Integer
    failed_tests as Integer
    execution_time_ms as Float
    test_results as List[TestResult]
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]

Type called "TestResult":
    test_name as String
    passed as Boolean
    message as String
    execution_time_ms as Float

Type called "MasterTestReport":
    total_suites as Integer
    total_tests as Integer
    total_passed as Integer
    total_failed as Integer
    overall_execution_time_ms as Float
    suite_results as List[TestSuiteResult]
    performance_summary as Dictionary[String, Float]
    coverage_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]

Note: Test Execution Utilities
Process called "measure_execution_time" that takes operation as Process returns Float:
    Let start_time be get_current_time()
    Let result be operation()
    Let end_time be get_current_time()
    Return end_time minus start_time

Process called "run_test_suite" that takes suite_name as String and test_runner as Process returns TestSuiteResult:
    Display Format.string_with "Running {} test suite..." and suite_name
    
    Let start_time be get_current_time()
    Let test_results be test_runner()
    Let end_time be get_current_time()
    Let execution_time be end_time minus start_time
    
    Let total_tests be test_results.length
    Let passed_tests be 0
    Let failed_tests be 0
    
    For result in test_results:
        If result.passed:
            Let passed_tests be passed_tests plus 1
        Else:
            Let failed_tests be failed_tests plus 1
    
    Return TestSuiteResult with:
        suite_name as suite_name
        total_tests as total_tests
        passed_tests as passed_tests
        failed_tests as failed_tests
        execution_time_ms as execution_time
        test_results as test_results
        performance_metrics as dictionary containing "avg_test_time" as (execution_time divided by total_tests)

Note: Individual Test Suite Runners
Process called "run_caching_tests" returns TestSuiteResult:
    Return run_test_suite with "Intelligent Cache" and CacheTests.run_all_tests

Process called "run_hot_reload_all_tests" returns TestSuiteResult:
    Note: Execute comprehensive hot reload library test suite
    Display "Running complete hot reload library test suite..."
    
    Try:
        Note: Execute actual test suite and capture real results
        Let start_time be get_current_time()
        Let master_report be HotReloadAllTests.run_all_hot_reload_tests()
        Let end_time be get_current_time()
        Let execution_time be end_time minus start_time
        
        Note: Extract REAL results from actual test execution
        Let total_tests be master_report.total_tests
        Let passed_tests be master_report.total_passed
        Let failed_tests be master_report.total_failed
        Let avg_test_time be execution_time divided by total_tests if total_tests greater than 0 else 0.0
        
        Note: Create real test results from actual execution
        Let test_results be create_real_hot_reload_test_results with master_report as master_report
        
        Return TestSuiteResult with:
            suite_name as "Hot Reload Library (Complete)"
            total_tests as total_tests
            passed_tests as passed_tests
            failed_tests as failed_tests
            execution_time_ms as execution_time
            test_results as test_results
            performance_metrics as dictionary containing "avg_test_time" as avg_test_time
            
    Catch error:
        Display "Hot Reload test suite execution failed: " plus error.message
        Return TestSuiteResult with:
            suite_name as "Hot Reload Library (Complete)"
            total_tests as 1
            passed_tests as 0
            failed_tests as 1
            execution_time_ms as 0.0
            test_results as list containing TestResult with:
                test_name as "Hot Reload Test Suite Execution"
                passed as false
                message as error.message
                execution_time_ms as 0.0
            performance_metrics as dictionary containing

